{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AJBV2GDZgLKXXB73YoesyB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that:\n1. Prometheus is running on port 9090 internally, but exposed on port 8000 via a service\n2. The `--web.enable-lifecycle` flag is enabled, so I can use `curl -X POST http://prometheus:8000/-/reload` to reload the config without restarting\n3. The config only scrapes itself at `localhost:9090`\n\nI need to update the Prometheus config to scrape all 3 RabbitMQ pods. I have a few options:\n\n1. **Static targets** - List all 3 RabbitMQ pod IPs explicitly. \n\nBut pod IPs are ephemeral and change when pods restart. A headless service like `rabbitmq-headless` could resolve to all pod IPs, but Prometheus would need to handle DNS service discovery. The better approach is using `kubernetes_sd_configs` with the pod role, which automatically discovers all RabbitMQ pods by their labels—this is a native Prometheus feature that doesn't require any CRDs. The catch is that Prometheus needs the right RBAC permissions to query the Kubernetes API.\n\nLooking at the current setup, there's no service account specified for Prometheus, so it's using the default one, which typically lacks the permissions to list pods or endpoints. I could either create a proper ServiceAccount with ClusterRole and ClusterRoleBinding to grant those permissions, or take a simpler route by using static DNS targets pointing directly to the three StatefulSet pods: `rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.{namespace}.svc.cluster.local:15692` and so on. Since the pod names are predictable with StatefulSets, the static DNS approach avoids the RBAC complexity. The Prometheus service runs on port 8000 externally but listens on 9090 internally. I can trigger a config reload by posting to the lifecycle endpoint after updating the ConfigMap, or I could just restart the Prometheus pod to pick up the changes.\n\nNow I need to check what labels are on the RabbitMQ pods to understand how they're organized.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1393,"cache_read_input_tokens":29959,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1393},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"43c0f111-d39d-4f85-9c65-833fe85c126c","uuid":"7b72f3dc-970b-4dc8-8493-ac56916e784e","request_id":"req_011CcbwNis8k68FRfFjekNz6"}
